Afropop singer Davido has insisted nobody can arrest him over his comment on the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) delegates election in Osun State. Davido alleged thugs have been imported to disrupt the Osun PDP primary slated for Saturday. The singer tweeted: “It has been brought to my attention that certain individuals have imported thugs and their mercenaries to our dear state to intimidate delegates, I will like to reassure Imole supporters and All Adhoc delegates that there is nothing to fear.” The singer, who refused to mention any name, alleged a politician he loves with all his heart was behind the attempt to disrupt the exercise. According to him: “It hurts sha … a certain politician that I love with all my heart and look up to so much is the one trynna fuck us up … but with God nothing dey sup ! IMOLE DE!!”   Battle for APC top posts shift to zones     UPDATED: Five feared killed as robbers attack three banks in…     PHOTOS: Jubilation as Tinubu visits Owa Obokun   A Twitter user Babawale dared him to mention the name of the alleged politician behind the act. Responding, the DMW boss boldly wrote the name of Oyo Governor, tagging his Twitter handle alongside. “@seyiamakinde,” he tweeted. Another concerned Twitter user with the handle @Captain_flexy said Davido will be arrested for making such allegations against Makinde. Reacting, the 29-year-old music star dared anyone to come to London and arrest him. He wrote: “Arrest who? In which Nigeria?? Make dem come carry me for @TheO2 na.”